How to get Codefoundry app running

1. 	Check out the code

2. 	Make a config/database.yml
	  SQLite is fine
		Make a dummy rails app somewhere else, copy the database.yml generated in
		the dummy app to codefoundry's config

3.	In config/settings.yml
		Add the following:
		development:
			...
			...
			marker:
				link_base: /
			repository_base_path: /absolute/path/to/a/sample/git/folder

4.  bundle install
5. 	rake db:create
6.	rake db:migrate
7.	rails s

App should be able to run with the above steps.

